Most works
                        (Liu et al., 2018a;
                        Parmar et al., 2018;
                        Child et al., 2019;
                        Huang et al., 2019;
                        Ho et al., 2019;
                        Wang et al., 2020a;
                        Hu et al., 2019;
                        Ramachandran et al., 2019;
                        Qiu et al., 2019;
                        Beltagy et al., 2020;
                        Ainslie et al., 2020;
                        Zaheer et al., 2020)
                        follow this paradigm.

To compensate,
                        Child et al. (2019);
                        Huang et al. (2019);
                        Ho et al. (2019);
                        Wang et al. (2020a)
                        attend key elements at fixed intervals to significantly increase the receptive field on keys.

Beltagy et al. (2020);
Ainslie et al. (2020);
Zaheer et al. (2020)
allow a small number of special tokens having access to all key elements.

Zaheer et al. (2020);
Qiu et al. (2019)
also add some pre-fixed sparse attention patterns to attend distant key elements directly.

Katharopoulos et al. (2020);
Choromanski et al. (2020)
rewrite the calculation of selfattention through kernelization approximation.

